      <h2>30 Software Testing Types</h2>
      <p>Click any item to expand its one-liner.</p>
      <div class="grid">
        <details><summary>Accessibility</summary><p>Inclusive use with assistive tech; WCAG checks and keyboard flows.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Performance</summary><p>Response times, throughput, and resource usage under load.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Functional</summary><p>Validates features against requirements and user stories.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Regression</summary><p>Confirms new changes do not break existing behavior.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Smoke</summary><p>High-level checks to verify the build is stable.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Black Box</summary><p>Tests via inputs/outputs without code knowledge.</p></details>
        <details><summary>White Box</summary><p>Tests with awareness of code structure and logic.</p></details>
