  <!-- APPROACH -->
  <section id="approach">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>My Test Approach</h2>
      <ol style="line-height:1.9;padding-left:1.2rem;">
        <li>Understand the user story, risks, and acceptance criteria.</li>
        <li>Plan light charters and checklists; prioritize by risk and impact.</li>
        <li>Automate critical paths (API + E2E smoke) to keep feedback fast.</li>
        <li>Expand coverage near code with unit/integration tests.</li>
        <li>Explore with session-based testing to uncover edge cases.</li>
        <li>Shift left with code reviews and CI gates.</li>
        <li>Measure pass rate, flakiness, and time-to-detect in CI.</li>
        <li>Report clearly with repro steps, expected/actual, logs, screenshots.</li>
        <li>Turn bugs into tests to prevent regressions.</li>
        <li>Continuously prune flaky tests and improve test data.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

